Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.99,0:00:06.49,Default,,0,0,0,,As Jehovah’s Witnesses, \Nwe truly love the Bible. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.49,0:00:08.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Why? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.49,0:00:11.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Because we know it is God’s Word. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.39,0:00:15.20,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s why we love reading it, \Nwe love studying it, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.20,0:00:18.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and we love learning about its history. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.17,0:00:21.47,Default,,0,0,0,,When we pause \Nfor a moment and reflect on \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.47,0:00:24.84,Default,,0,0,0,,the many efforts that have been made \Nthrough the centuries \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.84,0:00:29.25,Default,,0,0,0,,to hinder and even stop \Nthe distribution of the Bible, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.25,0:00:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,it becomes obvious \Nthat its Author, Jehovah, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.92,0:00:37.29,Default,,0,0,0,,has been personally involved \Nin preserving \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.29,0:00:40.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and making known \Nhis precious Word. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.32,0:00:43.33,Default,,0,0,0,,This is very much \Nin harmony with the thought \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.33,0:00:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,in Isaiah 40:8: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.80,0:00:49.87,Default,,0,0,0,,“The green grass dries up, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.87,0:00:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,“the blossom withers, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.40,0:00:57.64,Default,,0,0,0,,but the word\Nof our God endures forever.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.64,0:00:59.41,Default,,0,0,0,,With that in mind, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.41,0:01:01.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m happy to speak \Nwith you this month \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.75,0:01:05.32,Default,,0,0,0,,on a theme \Nthat’s very close to my heart:\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.32,0:01:09.32,Default,,0,0,0,,“The Word of Our God Endures Forever.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.32,0:01:13.89,Default,,0,0,0,,The more we come to appreciate \Nthe value of God’s Word, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.89,0:01:16.53,Default,,0,0,0,,the more we’ll be moved to read it\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.53,0:01:21.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and, even more important, \Nto apply it in our lives.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.97,0:01:26.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah gave us an outstanding gift \Nwhen he inspired \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.10,0:01:30.11,Default,,0,0,0,,faithful men \Nto record his precious Word. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.11,0:01:33.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s through the pages of God’s Word \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.08,0:01:37.48,Default,,0,0,0,,that we learn \Njust how much God loves us. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.48,0:01:41.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Thus, his Word contains \Nguidance on how to live. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.18,0:01:45.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It outlines his purpose \Nin creating us. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.09,0:01:49.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It gives us his precious promises \Nfor life everlasting \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.46,0:01:51.90,Default,,0,0,0,,in peace and happiness. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.90,0:01:55.63,Default,,0,0,0,,No wonder the apostle Paul \Nwas inspired to write \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.63,0:02:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,at 2 Timothy 3:16, 17: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.27,0:02:05.04,Default,,0,0,0,,“All Scripture is inspired of God \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.04,0:02:08.95,Default,,0,0,0,,“and beneficial for teaching, \Nfor reproving, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.95,0:02:13.88,Default,,0,0,0,,“for setting things straight, \Nfor disciplining in righteousness, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.88,0:02:17.69,Default,,0,0,0,,“so that the man of God \Nmay be fully competent, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.69,0:02:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,completely equipped for every good work.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.13,0:02:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, Satan the Devil \Ndoes not want people to have access \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.36,0:02:31.53,Default,,0,0,0,,to these precious truths \Nfrom our heavenly Father, Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.53,0:02:35.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s no surprise \Nthat there have been many obstacles \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.31,0:02:37.61,Default,,0,0,0,,to making the Bible available. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.61,0:02:41.48,Default,,0,0,0,,While Satan may not have been \Ndirectly behind all of these, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.48,0:02:45.05,Default,,0,0,0,,he certainly \Nhas made use of them. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.05,0:02:47.55,Default,,0,0,0,,What are some \Nof these obstacles, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.55,0:02:50.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and how have they been overcome?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.25,0:02:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s consider the first obstacle: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.19,0:02:55.89,Default,,0,0,0,,language barriers.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.89,0:02:58.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The first 39 books of the Bible, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.53,0:03:01.30,Default,,0,0,0,,which are often called the Old Testament, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.30,0:03:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,were written primarily \Nin the Hebrew language. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.00,0:03:07.30,Default,,0,0,0,,These books were known \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.30,0:03:10.64,Default,,0,0,0,,by Hebrew-speaking servants of Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.64,0:03:13.44,Default,,0,0,0,,However, as time went on,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.44,0:03:16.71,Default,,0,0,0,,particularly after \Nthe destruction of Babylon, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.71,0:03:21.12,Default,,0,0,0,,many Jews established communities \Nin other nations of the earth. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.12,0:03:23.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Many of these Jews spoke Greek. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.99,0:03:26.52,Default,,0,0,0,,They no longer used Hebrew. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.52,0:03:30.39,Default,,0,0,0,,That meant that many Jews \Nno longer had access \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.39,0:03:34.10,Default,,0,0,0,,to the Scriptures in a language \Nthey could understand.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.10,0:03:36.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Consider what had happened. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.57,0:03:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,As Alexander the Great conquered \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.80,0:03:41.24,Default,,0,0,0,,more and more \Nof the then-known world, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.24,0:03:43.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Greek gradually became \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.34,0:03:46.41,Default,,0,0,0,,the common language \Nof commerce and government \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.41,0:03:48.58,Default,,0,0,0,,throughout his empire. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.58,0:03:51.21,Default,,0,0,0,,If the Bible \Nwas to be understood \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.21,0:03:54.28,Default,,0,0,0,,by the Jews and by Jewish proselytes \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.28,0:03:58.52,Default,,0,0,0,,who were scattered throughout \Nthis vast Greek-speaking territory, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.52,0:04:02.66,Default,,0,0,0,,it needed to be translated into Greek. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.66,0:04:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Beginning in about the year 250 B.C.E., \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.80,0:04:11.03,Default,,0,0,0,,the Hebrew Scriptures began \Nto be translated into Greek. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.03,0:04:15.20,Default,,0,0,0,,In time, that Greek translation \Ncame to be known \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.20,0:04:17.34,Default,,0,0,0,,as the Septuagint. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.34,0:04:21.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It was widely and frequently used \Nby the Christians \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.04,0:04:23.85,Default,,0,0,0,,in the first century who spoke Greek. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.85,0:04:28.12,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, the writers \Nof the Christian Greek Scriptures,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.12,0:04:30.79,Default,,0,0,0,,which is often called \Nthe New Testament, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.79,0:04:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,frequently quoted directly \Nfrom that translation.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.76,0:04:38.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So that obstacle had been overcome. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.76,0:04:42.93,Default,,0,0,0,,But there were many more \Nlanguage obstacles ahead. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.93,0:04:46.50,Default,,0,0,0,,As the Roman Empire \Nbegan to flourish, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.50,0:04:49.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Latin replaced Greek \Nas a common language. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.91,0:04:54.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Now it was necessary \Nto translate the Bible into Latin. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.38,0:04:59.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Some Latin translations \Nof the Bible books began to appear. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.88,0:05:04.82,Default,,0,0,0,,But it was in the year 405 C.E. \Nthat Jerome completed \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.82,0:05:08.46,Default,,0,0,0,,the definitive Latin translation \Nof the Bible. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.46,0:05:10.66,Default,,0,0,0,,It came to be known \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.66,0:05:12.66,Default,,0,0,0,,as the Latin Vulgate. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.66,0:05:15.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Jerome’s translation \Nwould become \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.73,0:05:18.77,Default,,0,0,0,,the standard Bible \Nused by Christendom \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.77,0:05:23.54,Default,,0,0,0,,for the next nearly 1,000 years. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.54,0:05:28.44,Default,,0,0,0,,However, Latin soon became \Nthe language of the learned and the elite, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.44,0:05:32.18,Default,,0,0,0,,so the common people \Ncould no longer understand \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.18,0:05:34.35,Default,,0,0,0,,the Bible’s message.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.35,0:05:39.22,Default,,0,0,0,,During that long period, \Nthere were sincere men \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.22,0:05:43.46,Default,,0,0,0,,that translated portions of the Bible \Ninto some additional languages, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.46,0:05:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,but these translations were, \Nof course, all made by hand. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.07,0:05:54.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Such handwritten copies of the Bible \Nwere rare and expensive. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.04,0:05:57.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, \Naccess to the Bible in vernacular, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.51,0:06:01.18,Default,,0,0,0,,or common languages, \N was very limited.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.18,0:06:04.28,Default,,0,0,0,,But language was not \Nthe only obstacle \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.28,0:06:07.78,Default,,0,0,0,,that threatened to prevent \Nthe distribution of God’s Word. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.78,0:06:10.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Consider a second factor: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.79,0:06:15.43,Default,,0,0,0,,direct opposition \Nto Bible translation and distribution \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.43,0:06:17.96,Default,,0,0,0,,from religious leaders.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.96,0:06:22.93,Default,,0,0,0,,That opposition \Nstarted to increase in 1229 \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.93,0:06:27.40,Default,,0,0,0,,when the local church \NCouncil of Toulouse decreed:\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.40,0:06:31.77,Default,,0,0,0,, “We prohibit also \Nthat the laity should be permitted \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.77,0:06:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to have the books \Nof the Old or the New Testament.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.78,0:06:41.48,Default,,0,0,0,,In 1234, \Nthe Council of Tarragona decreed: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.48,0:06:46.22,Default,,0,0,0,,“No one should possess the books \Nof the Old or the New Testament \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.22,0:06:48.42,Default,,0,0,0,,“in the vernacular [language], \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.42,0:06:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,“and if anyone possesses them, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.56,0:06:54.16,Default,,0,0,0,,“let him deliver them, within eight days \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.16,0:06:56.93,Default,,0,0,0,,“from the promulgation of this decree, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.93,0:07:01.47,Default,,0,0,0,,to the local bishop, \Nso that they may be burned.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.47,0:07:06.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Thus, during \Na very long period in history, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.04,0:07:08.95,Default,,0,0,0,,there was limited access to the Bible \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.95,0:07:12.18,Default,,0,0,0,,in the languages \Nspoken by common people. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.18,0:07:15.18,Default,,0,0,0,,But did that mean \Nthat the Word of God \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.18,0:07:17.75,Default,,0,0,0,,would not continue to endure?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.75,0:07:20.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Neither language barriers \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.12,0:07:22.73,Default,,0,0,0,,nor opposition from religious leaders \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.73,0:07:26.76,Default,,0,0,0,,could stop God’s Word \Nfrom being made known. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.76,0:07:29.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Even in those dark times, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.33,0:07:32.47,Default,,0,0,0,,there were individuals \Nwho loved God’s Word \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.47,0:07:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and who worked hard \Nto translate it \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.20,0:07:38.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and to make it available to others. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.24,0:07:40.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Consider John Wycliffe \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.24,0:07:43.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and his followers \Nwho were called the Lollards.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.51,0:07:46.12,Default,,0,0,0,,John Wycliffe and his associates \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.12,0:07:48.25,Default,,0,0,0,,completed the translation \Nof the Bible \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.25,0:07:52.46,Default,,0,0,0,,into English \Nabout the year 1382. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.46,0:07:55.96,Default,,0,0,0,,They eagerly \Nhand copied the translation \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.96,0:07:58.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and then traveled \Nfrom village to village \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.43,0:08:01.83,Default,,0,0,0,,reading the Bible \Nto the common people. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.83,0:08:05.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Despite tremendous opposition \Nfrom the church, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.37,0:08:09.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Wycliffe and his followers \Nmade the Bible available \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.27,0:08:13.88,Default,,0,0,0,,to many honesthearted people \Nin the English language.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.88,0:08:18.25,Default,,0,0,0,,After Wycliffe died in 1384, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.25,0:08:21.48,Default,,0,0,0,,great opposition \Ncame to his followers. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.48,0:08:24.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Many had land \Nand property confiscated. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.85,0:08:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Others were burned \Nat the stake.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.16,0:08:32.80,Default,,0,0,0,,In response to the work \Nof Wycliffe and the Lollards, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.80,0:08:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,in 1408, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.96,0:08:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Thomas Arundel, \NArchbishop of Canterbury, declared: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.20,0:08:44.27,Default,,0,0,0,,“We therefore decree and ordain \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.27,0:08:49.21,Default,,0,0,0,,“that no man shall, hereafter, \Nby his own authority, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.21,0:08:52.28,Default,,0,0,0,,“translate any text of the Scripture \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.28,0:08:55.38,Default,,0,0,0,,“into English, \Nor any other tongue, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.38,0:09:00.36,Default,,0,0,0,,. . . upon pain \Nof greater excommunication.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.36,0:09:03.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Did such opposition \Nwipe out efforts \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.39,0:09:06.63,Default,,0,0,0,,to translate and make \Nthe Bible available? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.63,0:09:09.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Absolutely not! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.07,0:09:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The work of Wycliffe \Nand his associates \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.00,0:09:15.40,Default,,0,0,0,,stimulated interest in the Bible \Nthroughout England \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.40,0:09:19.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and even as far as central Europe. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.01,0:09:24.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Religious leaders were not able \Nto silence the Word of God.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.01,0:09:28.95,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, within just a few decades \Nafter Wycliffe’s death, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.95,0:09:32.69,Default,,0,0,0,,two factors \Nled to a tremendous increase \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.69,0:09:35.63,Default,,0,0,0,,in the availability \Nof the Bible. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.63,0:09:39.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The first, \Nabout the year 1454, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.26,0:09:43.50,Default,,0,0,0,,was the development \Nof printing with movable type. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.50,0:09:47.67,Default,,0,0,0,,This invention would \Nin time allow for the printing \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.67,0:09:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,of large quantities \Nof Bibles in many languages.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.48,0:09:57.41,Default,,0,0,0,,The second factor was \Nthe compiling and printing \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.41,0:10:01.32,Default,,0,0,0,,of the Hebrew and Greek \Noriginal language text \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.32,0:10:03.32,Default,,0,0,0,,of the Holy Scriptures. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.32,0:10:05.76,Default,,0,0,0,,This allowed many translators \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.76,0:10:09.29,Default,,0,0,0,,to have access \Nto the original language texts \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.29,0:10:11.43,Default,,0,0,0,,so that they then could produce \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.43,0:10:15.63,Default,,0,0,0,,high-quality translations \Nin their own languages.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.63,0:10:17.77,Default,,0,0,0,,What was the result? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.77,0:10:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,In the 1500’s across Europe, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.44,0:10:24.91,Default,,0,0,0,,fresh translations \Nwere made and printed \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.91,0:10:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,in vernacular, \Nor common languages, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.44,0:10:31.65,Default,,0,0,0,,including German, English, Italian, French, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.65,0:10:35.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Dutch, Czech, Danish, Swedish, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.45,0:10:39.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Spanish, Slovenian, and many others.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.32,0:10:43.19,Default,,0,0,0,,However, opposition continued. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.19,0:10:47.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Bible translators were frequently hounded \Nby the Inquisition, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.90,0:10:52.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and some translators like \NWilliam Tyndale and John Rogers \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.60,0:10:55.74,Default,,0,0,0,,were even put to death \Nfor their work. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.74,0:11:00.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Nonetheless, the Word of God \Ncontinued to endure \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.08,0:11:04.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and be made available \Nto more and more language groups.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.71,0:11:07.45,Default,,0,0,0,,By the early 1800’s, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.45,0:11:10.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Bible translation \Nbegan to speed up. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.59,0:11:14.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Bible societies \Nand intrepid translators \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.16,0:11:17.23,Default,,0,0,0,,began to work \Nin many parts of the earth \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.23,0:11:20.40,Default,,0,0,0,,so that the Bible began \Nto appear in languages \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.40,0:11:24.20,Default,,0,0,0,,of Asia, Africa, \Nthe Pacific islands, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.20,0:11:28.34,Default,,0,0,0,,as well as in indigenous languages \Nof the Americas. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.34,0:11:32.21,Default,,0,0,0,,From 1800 to 1899, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.21,0:11:35.11,Default,,0,0,0,,some portions of the Bible \Nwere translated \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.11,0:11:38.08,Default,,0,0,0,,into some 400 languages, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.08,0:11:40.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and from 1900 to 1950, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.92,0:11:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,more than 500 languages \Nwere added.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.42,0:11:50.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Consider what has been accomplished \Nwith the New World Translation. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.26,0:11:53.80,Default,,0,0,0,,As of this month, \Nthe New World Translation \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.80,0:11:56.97,Default,,0,0,0,,has been produced \Nin whole or in part \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.97,0:12:00.17,Default,,0,0,0,,in 149 languages, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.17,0:12:04.21,Default,,0,0,0,,with an additional \N37 languages approved.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.21,0:12:08.21,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s obvious \Nthat neither language barriers \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.21,0:12:11.11,Default,,0,0,0,,nor opposition \Nfrom religious leaders \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.11,0:12:14.92,Default,,0,0,0,,was able to stop \Nthe distribution of God’s Word. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.92,0:12:19.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah has protected it \Nthrough the ages. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.42,0:12:24.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s just as Psalm 12:6, 7 says: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.76,0:12:28.53,Default,,0,0,0,,“The sayings of Jehovah are pure; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.53,0:12:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,“they are like silver refined \Nin an earthen furnace, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.40,0:12:35.30,Default,,0,0,0,,“purified seven times. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.30,0:12:38.17,Default,,0,0,0,,“You will guard them, O Jehovah; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.17,0:12:40.64,Default,,0,0,0,,“you will protect each one of them \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.64,0:12:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,from this generation forever.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.05,0:12:49.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, Jehovah \Nhas protected each one \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.15,0:12:52.76,Default,,0,0,0,,of his precious sayings \Ndown through the ages.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.76,0:12:56.26,Default,,0,0,0,,But consider a third obstacle. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.26,0:13:00.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Although the Bible is now available \Nin whole or in part \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.43,0:13:03.57,Default,,0,0,0,,in almost 3,000 languages, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.57,0:13:07.14,Default,,0,0,0,,many people are no longer interested \Nin reading it. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.14,0:13:10.64,Default,,0,0,0,,In our modern age, \Npeople have become\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.64,0:13:13.68,Default,,0,0,0,,increasingly skeptical and irreligious. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.68,0:13:16.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Scientists have extolled \Nthe theory of evolution \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.98,0:13:19.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and have made it appear intelligent \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.35,0:13:21.95,Default,,0,0,0,,to doubt the existence of God. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.95,0:13:23.95,Default,,0,0,0,,At the same time, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.95,0:13:26.62,Default,,0,0,0,,secular philosophy has encouraged people \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.62,0:13:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,to make life decisions \Naccording to what feels right to them. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.96,0:13:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the result? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.00,0:13:35.97,Default,,0,0,0,,A world where people \Nare often guided \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.97,0:13:39.80,Default,,0,0,0,,by their own selfish, fleshly desires. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.80,0:13:42.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead of leading to happiness, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.04,0:13:46.51,Default,,0,0,0,,many people are left \Nfeeling empty and dissatisfied.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.51,0:13:50.78,Default,,0,0,0,,How is this third obstacle overcome? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.78,0:13:52.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Around the world, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.68,0:13:56.15,Default,,0,0,0,,people are opening \NGod’s Word, the Bible, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.15,0:13:58.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and reading it \Nfor themselves. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.39,0:14:01.49,Default,,0,0,0,,They’re recognizing \Nthat its thoughts \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.49,0:14:03.79,Default,,0,0,0,,are not simply human wisdom. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.79,0:14:07.53,Default,,0,0,0,,As they apply \Nits principles in their lives, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.53,0:14:10.17,Default,,0,0,0,,they find \Ncontentment and joy. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.17,0:14:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,They develop \Nself-respect and dignity \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.00,0:14:17.54,Default,,0,0,0,,from living according to \Nthe upright moral standards \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.54,0:14:19.81,Default,,0,0,0,,outlined by our Creator. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.81,0:14:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,As Psalm 119:97-100 states: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.32,0:14:28.92,Default,,0,0,0,,“How I do love your law! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.92,0:14:32.52,Default,,0,0,0,,“I ponder over it all day long. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.52,0:14:36.43,Default,,0,0,0,,“Your commandment \Nmakes me wiser than my enemies, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.43,0:14:39.03,Default,,0,0,0,,“because it is with me forever. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.03,0:14:42.53,Default,,0,0,0,,“I have more insight \Nthan all my teachers, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.53,0:14:45.77,Default,,0,0,0,,“because I ponder over your reminders. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.77,0:14:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,“I act with more understanding \Nthan older men, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.64,0:14:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,because I observe your orders.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.21,0:14:56.41,Default,,0,0,0,,What a powerful proof \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.41,0:15:00.08,Default,,0,0,0,,that the Word of God endures forever. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.08,0:15:04.45,Default,,0,0,0,,While the advice of human philosophers \Nis frequently flawed, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.45,0:15:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,the Bible’s counsel works. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.92,0:15:09.93,Default,,0,0,0,,If we apply it, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.93,0:15:13.56,Default,,0,0,0,,it can help us either \Nto overcome or to cope \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.56,0:15:17.50,Default,,0,0,0,,with any problem \Nor situation that we may face. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.50,0:15:19.50,Default,,0,0,0,,What is more, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.50,0:15:23.11,Default,,0,0,0,,by explaining \NGod’s purpose for the future, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.11,0:15:25.17,Default,,0,0,0,,it gives us a solid hope \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.17,0:15:29.21,Default,,0,0,0,,this earth will be restored \Nto the Paradise \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.21,0:15:31.81,Default,,0,0,0,,that it was \Nwhen it was first created. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.81,0:15:36.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It will be filled \Nwith peace and righteousness. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.12,0:15:38.59,Default,,0,0,0,,What a wonderful gift \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.59,0:15:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah gave us through the Bible! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.76,0:15:46.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, languages barriers, \Nopposition from religious leaders,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.33,0:15:49.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and even \Nan increasingly irreligious world \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.87,0:15:52.64,Default,,0,0,0,,cannot stop God’s Word.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.64,0:15:55.84,Default,,0,0,0,,How can you be part \Nof the evidence \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.84,0:15:58.91,Default,,0,0,0,,that the Word of God \Nendures forever? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.91,0:16:02.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Read it every day, \Nstudy it, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.91,0:16:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,meditate on the deep thoughts \Nthat it contains, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.72,0:16:11.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and then apply \Nthose priceless teachings in your life.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.62,0:16:16.09,Default,,0,0,0,,In this way, \Nnot just on the printed page, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.09,0:16:19.19,Default,,0,0,0,,not just on the library shelf, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.19,0:16:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,but in our minds, \Nin our own hearts, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.00,0:16:25.03,Default,,0,0,0,,in our own lives \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.03,0:16:28.05,Default,,0,0,0,,the Word of God \Nwill truly endure forever.\N
